    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "0bdedd1cfe6de1df",
      "text": "In the neuron’s case, a pulse must either be triggered down the output nerve (the axon) or not. For the manager, the fundamental task is also to say yes or no. It is true that managers do not spend their lives uttering these two words; they may never utter them. None the less, this is their task — and the subtleties, the nuances, the might-I-suggests and the perhaps-you-woulds are really socially intricate ways of saying yes or no."
